main event: An observer reported sighting a UFO and took photographs, but the original negatives were not received for analysis.
interesting points: The conclusion of the case was insufficient data for evaluation., No photographs were included in the report., A questionnaire was attached for the observer to complete to assist in the analysis., The observer was advised that original negatives were necessary for an evaluation., The sighting involved an object that appeared light and was about 30 feet wide, observed for about 5 minutes.
witness description: Observer with a reported UFO photograph but no negative received.
